<p class="">The House is always very ready to accept an apology by any Member who frankly admits that he has made an error, but there is a matter which arises on which, I think, we must ask for something <span id="960" class="column-number" data-column-number="960"></span> more definite. The hon. Member for Mid-Bedfordshire (Mr. Lennox-Boyd) made a certain statement. That statement has been taken very widely to be a representation of the policy of the Government. The hon. Member affected to know the mind of the Prime Minister.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
